<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900509-0045</DOCNO><DOCID>900509-0045.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Southwest Gas Corp.:   Net in Quarter Declined 5%   As Gas, Thrift Profits Fell</HL><DATE>05/09/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   SWX</CO><IN>EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Southwest Gas Corp.'s first-quarter net income fell 5% to$21.3 million, or $1.08 a share, due to lower earnings fromgas operations and from the company's thrift unit.   In the year-ago quarter, Las Vegas, Nev.-based SouthwestGas had net income of $22.5 million, or $1.17 a share. Thecompany had about 19.4 million average shares outstanding inthe latest quarter, compared with about 18.8 million a yearago.</LP><TEXT>   Revenue rose 6% to $273.6 million from $258.3 million.   Southwest said its gas operations contributed $20 millionto net income in the latest quarter, compared with $20.7million a year earlier. The company blamed the dip on costsrelated to pipeline replacement programs and facilitiesexpansion to meet increased natural gas demand.   The thrift unit, PriMerit Bank, contributed $1.3 millionto consolidated net income, compared with $1.8 million a yearago. The 36% decline was mainly due to lower real-estatedevelopment income and increased expenses related toexpansion of the thrift's branch networks in Nevada andArizona, the company said.</TEXT></DOC>